@startuml
title Viaverse Payment / Wallet — Sequence Diagram

actor Requester
participant "Requester Client" as Client
participant "API Gateway / App BFF" as BFF
participant "marketplace-service" as Marketplace
participant "payment-service" as Payment
participant "iyzico / Stripe Adapter" as Provider
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
queue "Outbox / Kafka" as Kafka
participant "notification-service" as Notification

Requester -> Client : accept quote
Client -> BFF : POST /quotes/{id}/accept
BFF -> Marketplace : acceptQuote
Marketplace -> DB : QuoteAccepted + JobCreated draft
Marketplace -> Kafka : QuoteAccepted / JobCreated

Client -> BFF : POST /payment-sessions
BFF -> Payment : createPaymentSession
Payment -> Marketplace : validate job/amount
Marketplace --> Payment : valid
Payment -> Provider : create checkout / authorize token
Payment -> DB : store PaymentSession
Provider --> Client : checkout redirect/result

Provider -> Payment : provider callback
Payment -> Provider : verify provider reference
Payment -> Payment : verify signature/amount/currency/idempotency
Payment -> DB : idempotent state update
Payment -> Kafka : PaymentAuthorized / PaymentFailed
Kafka -> Marketplace : payment state update event
Kafka -> Notification : notify participants

note bottom
Provider callback is the source for final payment state,
but only after signature/reference/amount/currency verification and idempotency check.
end note
@enduml
